24:49.826 --> 25:01.522
And as much of a burden as that was, there was also a joy, a blessing to be able to be the grandson who said, you know what, grandma, you took so much care of me when I was little.

25:01.783 --> 25:07.471
She was the one who when my mom, grandma would have to go to work and leave me home.

25:07.871 --> 25:12.658
She was the one who would come and care for me and babysit, if you will.

25:12.866 --> 25:16.072
And so she would take me to Disneyland out in California.

25:16.132 --> 25:23.245
She would take me on the trips because the woman who raised me, my grandmother, she had to work.

25:23.265 --> 25:24.568
She worked 18 hours a day.

25:24.588 --> 25:29.978
And so my great grandmother, Dorothy, was the one who would take me everywhere.

25:29.998 --> 25:31.060
And she would do everything.

25:31.380 --> 25:33.063
She would take me to baseball games.

25:34.105 --> 25:36.690
Dodgers, not those other red guys.

25:40.450 --> 25:42.092
So there was a blessing in the burden.

25:42.152 --> 25:48.080
In the midst of the burden, there was a blessing to be able to say, hey, grandma, you did all of that for me.

25:48.120 --> 25:49.622
And so now I'm going to give back to you.

25:50.703 --> 25:51.604
I'm just going to do it.

25:53.967 --> 26:02.098
See pastors experience the same burden in the care for the souls of those that are under the ministry that God provided him.

26:03.170 --> 26:10.220
James actually warns us that not many should become pastors or teachers in chapter three and verse one of the book of James.

26:10.441 --> 26:18.873
He says, dear brothers and sisters, not many of you should become teachers in the church for we who teach will be judged more strictly.

26:21.036 --> 26:24.321
Pastoral ministry, whether you see this or not, is a burden.

26:27.065 --> 26:28.668
It is a burden that we bear.

26:31.292 --> 26:32.914
There are difficult days.

26:36.482 --> 26:39.089
but it's also the richest blessing that we could ever have.

26:40.733 --> 26:42.778
It is also one of the greatest joys.

26:43.119 --> 26:50.738
Some of the greatest joys outside my family have been in the church as a pastor.

26:51.042 --> 27:00.397
watching somebody give their heart and life to Jesus for the very first time after they've come to church for a week or two or 10 or 20 or years.

27:00.958 --> 27:04.725
And finally, the message of the Holy Spirit has broken through.

27:04.945 --> 27:08.851
And they've said, today is the day that I'm gonna give my heart and life to Jesus.

27:09.673 --> 27:12.477
And knowing that at that moment they're never gonna be the same.

27:15.663 --> 27:17.746
And somebody is praying.

27:18.914 --> 27:22.099
All of a sudden you hear the utterance of the Holy Spirit and through their voice.

27:24.162 --> 27:29.971
And the infilling of the Holy Spirit with the evidence of speaking in other tongues is coming forward.

27:31.213 --> 27:32.575
There's no greater joy than that.

27:33.336 --> 27:37.522
There's no greater joy than laying hands on somebody and them being healed.

27:44.194 --> 27:52.985
We ask that you would pray for your pastor's physical and mental health as he seeks to care for the souls of the church.

27:53.005 --> 27:55.709
Your soul and the souls that are around you.

27:56.730 --> 28:03.178
Raina writes, he says, serving and leading a church well, expands all of the pastor's energy.

28:03.579 --> 28:06.282
He is on call every day and every hour.

28:06.582 --> 28:12.690
Because the demands are so great on him, the pastor often neglects his own health and wellbeing.

28:13.122 --> 28:16.348
We should pray for our pastors' physical and mental health.

28:16.649 --> 28:21.398
He needs wisdom to know what to preach and teach and how to present God's Word.

28:21.658 --> 28:26.688
He needs wisdom dealing with us church members week after week.

28:30.495 --> 28:34.162
And so as we end this particular point,

28:34.498 --> 28:35.399
are two questions.

28:35.499 --> 28:46.269
Why do you think pastors often overlook their own physical and mental health and what are some practical ways you can pray for and encourage your pastor in these areas?

28:53.636 --> 28:54.197
As we close.

28:56.859 --> 28:58.581
Our pastors and our church leaders.

29:00.583 --> 29:03.666
And again, as I mentioned earlier, I said hour

29:06.050 --> 29:09.095
Again, I don't want you to think that today's message is self-serving.

29:12.661 --> 29:28.626
When I felt led of the spirit to teach this series to us about being a church member, this is just part of that lesson that was decided months ago.

29:31.554 --> 29:37.561
As I stated, I have a shepherd who shepherds me just as I shepherd this flock.

29:37.581 --> 29:40.004
These pastors carry a heavy burden.

29:40.064 --> 29:41.746
They need our prayers for their family.

29:42.007 --> 29:43.869
They need our prayers for protection.

29:44.109 --> 29:47.874
And they need our prayers for their physical and mental health.

29:52.019 --> 29:58.066
In like fashion, Rainer closes each of the chapters, each of the sections that he covers

29:58.210 --> 29:59.892
In the book, I am a church member.

30:00.272 --> 30:06.760
And again, if you would like a copy of that book and don't have it, I have extra copies in my office that I'm happy to give you.

30:06.981 --> 30:09.243
It's a very thin, very small book.

30:11.186 --> 30:15.371
He has a pledge for each of the messages.

30:17.894 --> 30:20.056
And the pledge for this one says this.

30:20.137 --> 30:21.919
It says, I am a church member.

30:22.039 --> 30:24.342
I will pray for my pastor every day.

30:24.782 --> 30:27.986
I understand that the pastor's work is never ending.

30:28.418 --> 30:33.465
His days are filled with numerous demands that bring emotional highs and lows.

30:34.186 --> 30:38.191
He must deal with critics, he must be a good husband and father.

30:38.973 --> 30:46.243
Because my pastor cannot do all things in his power, I will pray for his strength and wisdom daily.

30:49.667 --> 30:57.458
I can tell you as your pastor, whether you like me, you don't like me, you like the way I preach, you're not a big fan of the way I preach,

30:59.426 --> 31:00.347
I covet your prayers.

31:03.310 --> 31:11.277
There is a pressure of divine responsibility as the shepherd of a flock.

31:14.380 --> 31:25.091
When we ordain ministers in the assemblies of God, so if you're familiar, we have three levels of what we call ministerial credential.

31:26.152 --> 31:28.434
There is a certified minister

31:29.474 --> 31:31.357
and there is a licensed minister.

31:32.118 --> 31:37.667
Both of those are never intended to be held indefinitely.

31:37.687 --> 31:45.879
They are intended to be training ground, starting points, to lead to ordination.

31:46.080 --> 31:51.488
Because ordination is the only position in the Bible listed for ministers.

31:53.231 --> 31:55.314
And when we ordain a minister,

31:55.938 --> 32:02.528
In the Southern Missouri district, we are given, and I guess I could have wore mine, we are given what is called a mantle.

32:03.369 --> 32:19.954
And it's just a shawl, a little strip, and it's at the moment of ordination, the district leadership lays their hands on the minister, and then they place the mantle of leadership on the minister's shoulders.

32:23.010 --> 32:29.158
And Pastor Don has a story that he says, he's done this dozens and dozens and dozens of time.

32:29.479 --> 32:43.518
And he says, as those mantles are laid on the minister's shoulder, he said it is visible across the line that you see the minister's shoulder sink under the weight, under the pressure of wearing that mantle.

32:46.221 --> 32:52.850
So again, unless you think I'm just kind of moaning and groaning, there is a weight

32:53.026 --> 32:54.227
of being your shepherd.

32:56.911 --> 33:00.695
There is a weight of being my pastor, Pastor Don.

33:04.100 --> 33:08.465
And I know he covets my prayers, just as I covet your prayers.

33:08.525 --> 33:22.162
So here in just a moment, we're gonna, as we have been doing just for this series of I Am a Church, remember, we are going to prepare our hearts for communion.

33:22.306 --> 33:25.771
If somebody would go and notify the children's church, please.

33:29.236 --> 33:36.406
I want us to remember the importance of unity and support within our church body.

33:41.312 --> 33:45.338
Why are we taking communion every week when we talk about being a church member?

33:48.402 --> 33:51.186
Because there is a unity that happened at the table.

33:52.354 --> 33:58.521
On the night that Christ was betrayed, they took bread and they broke it.

34:00.223 --> 34:03.386
And he said, this is my body that is broken for you.

34:03.746 --> 34:06.630
As often as you do this, as often as you do what?

34:06.890 --> 34:09.413
You gather together, you come around the table.

34:09.673 --> 34:12.256
He says, do this in remembrance of me.

34:16.641 --> 34:18.002
And then at the end of dinner,

34:19.618 --> 34:23.745
He takes the cup and he says, as often as you do this, this is my blood.

34:24.126 --> 34:26.930
This is the new covenant that I am giving to you.

34:27.271 --> 34:32.199
As often as you drink of this, as often as you come together, do this in remembrance of me.

34:32.540 --> 34:36.446
There was a unity that happened at the table.

34:38.029 --> 34:43.538
There was a familiarity, a camaraderie, a joining together of the disciples.

34:44.674 --> 34:50.260
coming together as one, coming together as a unified group.

34:50.560 --> 34:57.487
And so as we have come and we talk about being church members, being a member of the church is about joining together.

34:58.909 --> 35:05.836
Being a church member isn't shouting your name on the legal line so that we can satisfy a federal government mandate.

35:06.757 --> 35:11.762
Being a member of the church is joining our hearts together.

35:12.130 --> 35:22.867
and locking arm in arm with other brothers and sisters and says, hey, listen, we're going to join together and we're going to sing and we're going to lift up the name of Jesus to the body of Christ.

35:22.887 --> 35:32.722
It's coming together and saying, hey, the group of us, we're going to lock together with them and we're going to teach and we're going to preach and we're going to bleed Sunday school and we're going to teach

35:32.770 --> 35:51.595
prayer meeting and whatever else it is, it's coming together and saying, hey, while you guys are doing that, I'm gonna go over here and I'm gonna hold on and I'm gonna shepherd Pastor, as Pastor Leticia shared with us one day, we're gonna shepherd the littlest of these because even though we're nursery workers, we are the very first pastor that these little ones ever have.

35:52.436 --> 35:55.841
And we come together because there is unity at the table.

35:58.525 --> 36:02.610
And so we come together and we take communion together.

36:04.642 --> 36:09.488
And so as we do that, communion is a time to reflect also on Christ's sacrifice.

36:10.929 --> 36:21.041
Because He did it for us to send us in unity to be His hands and feet in a lost and dying world.

36:23.223 --> 36:32.754
Just as we are nourished by the bread and the cup, let us nourish our pastors, our leaders,

36:34.146 --> 36:34.867
with our prayers.

36:39.151 --> 37:02.034
As we partake in communion, as we come together in unity, let's commit to hold our leaders, our pastors, our teachers up in prayer, committing ourselves to pray for them, just as Christ had committed Himself to us.

37:03.938 --> 37:05.580
So here's how today is gonna go.

37:05.620 --> 37:09.744
Each week we've done communion, we've done it a little bit different.

37:11.205 --> 37:23.577
Rather than settling into a simple routine, today for communion, we your pastors are gonna serve you communion today.

37:24.458 --> 37:28.182
Right where you're at, you can stay right where you're at, we're not gonna ask you to come down this time.

37:30.144 --> 37:32.626
See, we've asked you to serve us today

37:32.962 --> 37:33.943
by praying for us.

37:34.003 --> 37:36.507
We've asked you to hold us up in prayer.

37:39.631 --> 37:42.675
So today, we're gonna serve you.

37:45.018 --> 37:51.606
We're gonna come and bring the elements to you.

37:51.626 --> 37:53.549
So pastors, I've already spoken.

37:53.609 --> 37:56.032
If you'll come and take your place, I'll serve you in just a moment.

37:56.633 --> 37:58.095
You'll just come and stand at the altar.

37:58.936 --> 38:00.658
If everybody else will bow your heads,

38:01.154 --> 38:02.876
Let's pray over our communion time.

38:04.938 --> 38:11.686
Heavenly Father, we come before you with grateful hearts and thankful for the sacrifice of your Son, Jesus Christ.

38:12.707 --> 38:23.800
As we prepare to partake in this time, this communion, we remember that your body was broken and that your blood was shed for the forgiveness of our sins.

38:24.961 --> 38:29.586
Lord, we acknowledge this immense responsibility and pressures that

38:29.698 --> 38:34.525
Our pastors, our church leaders, our district, our national leaders carry.

38:34.766 --> 38:40.234
We lift them up to you now, asking for your divine protection, strength and wisdom.

38:41.135 --> 38:47.024
Father, we pray that you would surround their families with your love and peace, shielding them from the enemy's attacks.

38:47.324 --> 38:51.590
We ask that you would be everything that they need.

38:52.552 --> 38:59.442
And as we take this bread and drink it from this cup, may it be a reminder of our commitment to support

38:59.522 --> 39:01.324
and to pray for our leaders.

39:03.006 --> 39:05.368
Help us be united in love and purpose.

39:07.851 --> 39:12.076
Help us to serve one another selflessly as you have served us.

39:12.997 --> 39:17.762
Cleanse our hearts, renew our spirits, and draw us closer to you and to one another.

39:20.085 --> 39:23.929
Let this communion time be a reflection and renewal.

39:25.250 --> 39:28.754
Strengthening our bond as a church family

39:29.026 --> 39:31.533
and our dedication to your service.

39:31.553 --> 39:34.761
In the mighty name of Jesus, we pray.

39:35.483 --> 39:35.944
Amen.

39:36.526 --> 39:42.802
Amen.

